==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aërial sickness
<hw>A*⟦eum⟧"ri*al sick"ness</hw>. <def>A sickness felt by a⟦eum⟧ronauts
due to high speed of flights and rapidity in changing altitudes,
combining some symptoms of mountain sickness and some of seasickness.
The nauseous symptoms similar to seasickness experienced by passengers
in pressurized aircraft is called <altname>air
sickness</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>A⟦eum⟧riality</ent>⟦br⟧
